<font color="#FF0000">WHY WAS THE WAR FOUGHT?</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan 31 18:59:53 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
If the American government cared about freedom and democracy, why don't we have sanctions against Nigeria. Nigeria is one of the bloodthirsty regimes on the planet. Few people in the U.S. have heard of Nigeria, or could care less. Obviously nobody suggests we invade Nigeria. Nobody even suggests we have an embargo or sanctions against Nigeria. I'm just using this as an example. There are dozens of brutal dictatorships and monarchies all over the world with which the the United States has very friendly cordial relations. Why don't we have sanctions against Burma? We fought the Persian Gulf War to restore one of the only absolute monarchies on the planet. The people in Kuwait aren't any more free today than when they were part of Iraq.<br>
One of the tightest allies of the United States is Turkey. Turkey has engaged in genocide against Armenians, Greeks, and Kurds. Not only do they frequently round up and kill Kurds in their country, but they frequently invade surrounding countries to kill the Kurds in those countries also. Turkey is reknown for human rights abuses. Despite this, Turkey is one of our tightest allies. We support Indonesia. We support the monarchies of the Middle East. When Isreal fired missles into a U.N. base, killing over a hundred civilians, innocent refuges, and kept firing the missles after the U.N. officials begged them to stop, the United States refuses to even mildly verbally criticize Isreal. The United States overthrew the first democratically elected leader of Chile. The United States trained the death squads of El Salvador which slaughtered whole villages. Since when has the American government ever cared remotely about democracy or freedom anywhere in the world? The Vietnam War had absolutely nothing to do with democracy or freedom. It had absolutely nothing to do with any sort of compassion for the South Vietnamese people. We slaughtered<br>
two million Vietnamese. We fought the Vietnam War because the superpowers were fighting over the world. Each superpower wanted to control as much of the world as possible. Imagine a world map where all of the countries allied with a specific superpower are colored in one color. Each superpower wanted as much of the map to be colored in their color as possible.  That is the singular reason why the Vietnam War was fought.
